The paper presents a method for learning representations from electrocardiogram (ECG) data for a clinical task of classifying the origin of ventricular tachycardia (VT) into pre-defined segments. The method uses a conditional variational autoencoder (VAE) to extract subject-specific adjustments to the ECG data, conditioned on task-specific representations learned from a deterministic encoder. The paper involves machine learning techniques such as VAE, contrastive regularization, and maximum mean discrepancy. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper involves the application of machine learning techniques to a clinical task, which suggests the possibility of the paper belonging to cs.BIO (Computational Biology) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
